      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;uv-workspace&#34;&gt;uv workspace&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;A uv workspace is a folder that contains multiple Python projects (packages/apps) that are managed together with one top-level configuration.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Workspaces are useful when you have:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Several related services/packages (e.g. API, worker, common-lib)&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Shared dependencies / shared internal libraries&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Want to develop and test them together&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;For example, you can have:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;code-block code-line-numbers open&#34; style=&#34;counter-reset: code-block 0&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;code-header language-txt&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;span class=&#34;code-title&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;arrow fas fa-angle-right fa-fw&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;        &lt;span class=&#34;ellipses&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;fas fa-ellipsis-h fa-fw&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;        &lt;span class=&#34;copy&#34; title=&#34;Copy to clipboard&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;far fa-copy fa-fw&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-txt&#34; data-lang=&#34;txt&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;llm-platform/&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;  pyproject.toml          # workspace root&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;  api/&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;    pyproject.toml        # FastAPI app&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;  worker/&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;    pyproject.toml        # queue consumers, tasks&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;  common/&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;    pyproject.toml        # shared utilities, models&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;And uv understands that my-workspace is a workspace root and each project is a member.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
